Japan may further ease regulations
on tourist visa applications for Chinese visitors, aiming to tap
growing travel demand among the nationâ€™s emerging middle class,
the Nikkei newspaper said.  A relaxing of rules, which now require households to have
annual income of at least 100,000 yuan ($15,140), may come in
time for next summer after some deregulation last July increased
Chinese tourist numbers significantly, Nikkei reported, without
